{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":940,"text":"I want to share with you\nsomething my father taught me:"},{"time":5321,"text":"no condition is permanent."},{"time":9283,"text":"It's a lesson he shared with me\nagain and again,"},{"time":12191,"text":"and I learned it to be true the hard way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16590,"text":"Here I am in my fourth-grade class."},{"time":19531,"text":"This is my yearbook picture\ntaken in my class in school"},{"time":23289,"text":"in Monrovia, Liberia."},{"time":25514,"text":"My parents migrated from India\nto West Africa in the 1970s,"},{"time":29939,"text":"and I had the privilege\nof growing up there."},{"time":33772,"text":"I was nine years old,"},{"time":34946,"text":"I loved kicking around a soccer ball,"},{"time":36732,"text":"and I was a total math and science geek."},{"time":39003,"text":"I was living the kind of life\nthat, really, any child would dream of."},{"time":45280,"text":"But no condition is permanent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48346,"text":"On Christmas Eve in 1989,"},{"time":51293,"text":"civil war erupted in Liberia."},{"time":55082,"text":"The war started in the rural countryside,"},{"time":57060,"text":"and within months, rebel armies\nhad marched towards our hometown."},{"time":60791,"text":"My school shut down,"},{"time":62485,"text":"and when the rebel armies captured\nthe only international airport,"},{"time":65981,"text":"people started panicking and fleeing."},{"time":69750,"text":"My mom came knocking one morning\nand said, \"Raj, pack your things --"},{"time":73132,"text":"we have to go.\""},{"time":74995,"text":"We were rushed to the center of town,"},{"time":77248,"text":"and there on a tarmac,\nwe were split into two lines."},{"time":82633,"text":"I stood with my family in one line,"},{"time":85150,"text":"and we were stuffed into the cargo hatch"},{"time":87574,"text":"of a rescue plane."},{"time":89374,"text":"And there on a bench,\nI was sitting with my heart racing."},{"time":92285,"text":"As I looked out the open hatch,"},{"time":94728,"text":"I saw hundreds of Liberians\nin another line,"},{"time":97591,"text":"children strapped to their backs."},{"time":100514,"text":"When they tried to jump in with us,"},{"time":103384,"text":"I watched soldiers restrain them."},{"time":106691,"text":"They were not allowed to flee."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109177,"text":"We were the lucky ones."},{"time":111345,"text":"We lost what we had,"},{"time":113125,"text":"but we resettled in America,"},{"time":115561,"text":"and as immigrants, we benefitted\nfrom the community of supporters"},{"time":118716,"text":"that rallied around us."},{"time":121932,"text":"They took my family into their home,"},{"time":123759,"text":"they mentored me."},{"time":126096,"text":"And they helped my dad\nstart a clothing shop."},{"time":128263,"text":"I'd visit my father\non weekends as a teenager"},{"time":130656,"text":"to help him sell sneakers and jeans."},{"time":133134,"text":"And every time business would get bad,"},{"time":135491,"text":"he'd remind me of that mantra:"},{"time":137998,"text":"no condition is permanent."},{"time":140793,"text":"That mantra and my parents' persistence\nand that community of supporters"},{"time":145246,"text":"made it possible for me\nto go through college"},{"time":147595,"text":"and eventually to medical school."},{"time":150365,"text":"I'd once had my hopes crushed in a war,"},{"time":154037,"text":"but because of them,"},{"time":155329,"text":"I had a chance to pursue my dream\nto become a doctor."},{"time":159046,"text":"My condition had changed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162789,"text":"It had been 15 years\nsince I escaped that airfield,"},{"time":165450,"text":"but the memory of those two lines\nhad not escaped my mind."},{"time":168243,"text":"I was a medical student in my mid-20s,"},{"time":170787,"text":"and I wanted to go back"},{"time":172045,"text":"to see if I could serve\nthe people we'd left behind."},{"time":175785,"text":"But when I got back,"},{"time":176959,"text":"what I found was utter destruction."},{"time":178810,"text":"The war had left us with just 51 doctors"},{"time":180955,"text":"to serve a country of four million people."},{"time":183417,"text":"It would be like the city of San Francisco\nhaving just 10 doctors."},{"time":187409,"text":"So if you got sick in the city\nwhere those few doctors remain,"},{"time":190508,"text":"you might stand a chance."},{"time":191981,"text":"But if you got sick in the remote,\nrural rainforest communities,"},{"time":195871,"text":"where you could be days\nfrom the nearest clinic --"},{"time":198260,"text":"I was seeing my patients die\nfrom conditions no one should die from,"},{"time":202025,"text":"all because they were\ngetting to me too late."},{"time":204192,"text":"Imagine you have a two-year-old\nwho wakes up one morning with a fever,"},{"time":207638,"text":"and you realize she could have malaria,"},{"time":210066,"text":"and you know the only way to get her\nthe medicine she needs"},{"time":213091,"text":"would be to take her to the riverbed,"},{"time":214968,"text":"get in a canoe, paddle to the other side"},{"time":217067,"text":"and then walk for up to two days\nthrough the forest"},{"time":219706,"text":"just to reach the nearest clinic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222157,"text":"One billion people live\nin the world's most remote communities,"},{"time":225300,"text":"and despite the advances we've made\nin modern medicine and technology,"},{"time":228969,"text":"our innovations are not\nreaching the last mile."},{"time":231692,"text":"These communities have been left behind,"},{"time":233677,"text":"because they've been thought\ntoo hard to reach"},{"time":235900,"text":"and too difficult to serve."},{"time":238282,"text":"Illness is universal;"},{"time":239993,"text":"access to care is not."},{"time":242222,"text":"And realizing this lit a fire in my soul."},{"time":244808,"text":"No one should die because they live\ntoo far from a doctor or clinic."},{"time":249090,"text":"No condition should be permanent."},{"time":253361,"text":"And help in this case\ndidn't come from the outside,"},{"time":256028,"text":"it actually came from within."},{"time":257705,"text":"It came from the communities themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260178,"text":"Meet Musu."},{"time":261561,"text":"Way out in rural Liberia,"},{"time":262970,"text":"where most girls have not had\na chance to finish primary school,"},{"time":267163,"text":"Musu had been persistent."},{"time":270093,"text":"At the age of 18,\nshe completed high school,"},{"time":272438,"text":"and she came back to her community."},{"time":274738,"text":"She saw that none of the children\nwere getting treatment"},{"time":277434,"text":"for the diseases\nthey needed treatment for --"},{"time":279585,"text":"deadly diseases, like malaria\nand pneumonia."},{"time":281929,"text":"So she signed up to be a volunteer."},{"time":285839,"text":"There are millions of volunteers like Musu\nin rural parts around our world,"},{"time":289504,"text":"and we got to thinking --"},{"time":291301,"text":"community members like Musu\ncould actually help us solve a puzzle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296103,"text":"Our health care system\nis structured in such a way"},{"time":298804,"text":"that the work of diagnosing disease\nand prescribing medicines"},{"time":302536,"text":"is limited to a team of nurses\nand doctors like me."},{"time":306418,"text":"But nurses and doctors\nare concentrated in cities,"},{"time":309087,"text":"so rural communities like Musu's\nhave been left behind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312902,"text":"So we started asking some questions:"},{"time":314681,"text":"What if we could reorganize\nthe medical care system?"},{"time":317238,"text":"What if we could have community\nmembers like Musu"},{"time":320180,"text":"be a part or even be the center\nof our medical team?"},{"time":323481,"text":"What if Musu could help us bring\nhealth care from clinics in cities"},{"time":327430,"text":"to the doorsteps of her neighbors?"},{"time":331141,"text":"Musu was 48 when I met her."},{"time":334016,"text":"And despite her amazing talent and grit,"},{"time":337093,"text":"she hadn't had a paying job in 30 years."},{"time":341463,"text":"So what if technology could support her?"},{"time":344384,"text":"What if we could invest in her\nwith real training,"},{"time":348702,"text":"equip her with real medicines,"},{"time":351828,"text":"and have her have a real job?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":356404,"text":"Well, in 2007, I was trying\nto answer these questions,"},{"time":360892,"text":"and my wife and I were\ngetting married that year."},{"time":364100,"text":"We asked our relatives to forgo\nthe wedding registry gifts"},{"time":368617,"text":"and instead donate some money"},{"time":370191,"text":"so we could have some start-up money\nto launch a nonprofit."},{"time":374118,"text":"I promise you, I'm a lot\nmore romantic than that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376579,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":378163,"text":"We ended up raising $6,000,"},{"time":380580,"text":"teamed up with some\nLiberians and Americans"},{"time":382732,"text":"and launched a nonprofit\ncalled Last Mile Health."},{"time":385494,"text":"Our goal is to bring a health worker\nwithin reach of everyone, everywhere."},{"time":390421,"text":"We designed a three-step process --"},{"time":392379,"text":"train, equip and pay --"},{"time":393867,"text":"to invest more deeply\nin volunteers like Musu"},{"time":397248,"text":"to become paraprofessionals,"},{"time":398871,"text":"to become community health workers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401069,"text":"First we trained Musu to prevent,\ndiagnose and treat"},{"time":405650,"text":"the top 10 diseases afflicting\nfamilies in her village."},{"time":409903,"text":"A nurse supervisor visited her\nevery month to coach her."},{"time":413883,"text":"We equipped her with modern\nmedical technology,"},{"time":416448,"text":"like this $1 malaria rapid test,"},{"time":419842,"text":"and put it in a backpack\nfull of medicines like this"},{"time":423595,"text":"to treat infections like pneumonia,"},{"time":426590,"text":"and crucially,"},{"time":428181,"text":"a smartphone, to help her track\nand report on epidemics."},{"time":433340,"text":"Last, we recognized\nthe dignity in Musu's work."},{"time":436461,"text":"With the Liberian government,\nwe created a contract,"},{"time":438918,"text":"paid her"},{"time":440228,"text":"and gave her the chance\nto have a real job."},{"time":442345,"text":"And she's amazing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443538,"text":"Musu has learned over 30 medical skills,"},{"time":447048,"text":"from screening children for malnutrition,"},{"time":449831,"text":"to assessing the cause\nof a child's cough with a smartphone,"},{"time":453328,"text":"to supporting people with HIV"},{"time":456473,"text":"and providing follow-up care\nto patients who've lost their limbs."},{"time":461965,"text":"Working as part of our team,"},{"time":464074,"text":"working as paraprofessionals,"},{"time":465623,"text":"community health workers can help ensure"},{"time":467876,"text":"that a lot of what\nyour family doctor would do"},{"time":470197,"text":"reaches the places that most\nfamily doctors could never go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474041,"text":"One of my favorite things to do\nis to care for patients"},{"time":477006,"text":"with community health workers."},{"time":478479,"text":"So last year I was visiting A.B.,"},{"time":480816,"text":"and like Musu, A.B. had had\na chance to go to school."},{"time":484479,"text":"He was in middle school,\nin the eighth grade,"},{"time":487580,"text":"when his parents died."},{"time":488870,"text":"He became an orphan and had to drop out."},{"time":492919,"text":"Last year, we hired and trained\nA.B. as a community health worker."},{"time":498215,"text":"And while he was making\ndoor to door house calls,"},{"time":501105,"text":"he met this young boy named Prince,"},{"time":503352,"text":"whose mother had had trouble\nbreastfeeding him,"},{"time":506649,"text":"and by the age of six months,\nPrince had started to waste away."},{"time":509885,"text":"A.B. had just been taught how to use\nthis color-coded measuring tape"},{"time":513518,"text":"that wraps around the upper arm\nof a child to diagnose malnutrition."},{"time":517088,"text":"A.B. noticed that Prince\nwas in the red zone,"},{"time":519503,"text":"which meant he had to be hospitalized."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521418,"text":"So A.B. took Prince\nand his mother to the river,"},{"time":524084,"text":"got in a canoe"},{"time":525275,"text":"and paddled for four hours\nto get to the hospital."},{"time":527959,"text":"Later, after Prince was discharged,"},{"time":530982,"text":"A.B. taught mom how to feed baby\na food supplement."},{"time":535863,"text":"A few months ago,"},{"time":537926,"text":"A.B. took me to visit Prince,\nand he's a chubby little guy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541166,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":542321,"text":"He's meeting his milestones,\nhe's pulled himself up to a stand,"},{"time":545517,"text":"and is even starting to say a few words."},{"time":547498,"text":"I'm so inspired by these\ncommunity health workers."},{"time":550021,"text":"I often ask them why they do what they do,"},{"time":552333,"text":"and when I asked A.B.,"},{"time":554954,"text":"he said, \"Doc, since I dropped out\nof school, this is the first time"},{"time":558953,"text":"I'm having a chance\nto hold a pen to write."},{"time":562036,"text":"My brain is getting fresh.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":566104,"text":"The stories of A.B. and Musu\nhave taught me something fundamental"},{"time":569806,"text":"about being human."},{"time":572276,"text":"Our will to serve others"},{"time":575429,"text":"can actually help us\ntransform our own conditions."},{"time":579712,"text":"I was so moved by how powerful\nthe will to serve our neighbors can be"},{"time":583830,"text":"a few years ago,"},{"time":586004,"text":"when we faced a global catastrophe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588660,"text":"In December 2013,"},{"time":590386,"text":"something happened in the rainforests\nacross the border from us in Guinea."},{"time":593985,"text":"A toddler named Emile fell sick\nwith vomiting, fever and diarrhea."},{"time":598609,"text":"He lived in an area\nwhere the roads were sparse"},{"time":600942,"text":"and there had been massive\nshortages of health workers."},{"time":604832,"text":"Emile died,"},{"time":606012,"text":"and a few weeks later his sister died,"},{"time":607893,"text":"and a few weeks later his mother died."},{"time":609837,"text":"And this disease would spread\nfrom one community to another."},{"time":613036,"text":"And it wasn't until three months later"},{"time":615085,"text":"that the world recognized this as Ebola."},{"time":618304,"text":"When every minute counted,\nwe had already lost months,"},{"time":621026,"text":"and by then the virus had spread\nlike wildfire all across West Africa,"},{"time":624503,"text":"and eventually to other\nparts of the world."},{"time":626553,"text":"Businesses shut down,\nairlines started canceling routes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629875,"text":"At the height of the crisis,"},{"time":631315,"text":"when we were told that 1.4 million\npeople could be infected,"},{"time":635784,"text":"when we were told\nthat most of them would die,"},{"time":639311,"text":"when we had nearly lost all hope,"},{"time":643678,"text":"I remember standing with a group\nof health workers"},{"time":646574,"text":"in the rainforest where\nan outbreak had just happened."},{"time":649356,"text":"We were helping train and equip\nthem to put on the masks,"},{"time":652369,"text":"the gloves and the gowns that they needed"},{"time":654433,"text":"to keep themselves safe from the virus"},{"time":656452,"text":"while they were serving their patients."},{"time":658784,"text":"I remember the fear in their eyes."},{"time":662492,"text":"And I remember staying up at night,\nterrified if I'd made the right call"},{"time":668519,"text":"to keep them in the field."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670757,"text":"When Ebola threatened to bring\nhumanity to its knees,"},{"time":675496,"text":"Liberia's community health workers\ndidn't surrender to fear."},{"time":679779,"text":"They did what they had always done:"},{"time":682131,"text":"they answered the call\nto serve their neighbors."},{"time":685586,"text":"Community members across Liberia\nlearned the symptoms of Ebola,"},{"time":689378,"text":"teamed up with nurses and doctors\nto go door-to-door to find the sick"},{"time":692955,"text":"and get them into care."},{"time":694535,"text":"They tracked thousands of people\nwho had been exposed to the virus"},{"time":697969,"text":"and helped break\nthe chain of transmission."},{"time":700416,"text":"Some ten thousand community\nhealth workers risked their own lives"},{"time":703750,"text":"to help hunt down this virus\nand stop it in its tracks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707527,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":714696,"text":"Today, Ebola has come\nunder control in West Africa,"},{"time":718230,"text":"and we've learned a few things."},{"time":720349,"text":"We've learned that blind spots\nin rural health care"},{"time":722971,"text":"can lead to hot spots of disease,"},{"time":724793,"text":"and that places all of us at greater risk."},{"time":727702,"text":"We've learned that the most efficient\nemergency system"},{"time":730418,"text":"is actually an everyday system,"},{"time":732470,"text":"and that system has to reach\nall communities,"},{"time":735220,"text":"including rural communities like Emile's."},{"time":738540,"text":"And most of all,"},{"time":739715,"text":"we've learned from the courage\nof Liberia's community health workers"},{"time":743200,"text":"that we as people are not defined\nby the conditions we face,"},{"time":746945,"text":"no matter how hopeless they seem."},{"time":750140,"text":"We're defined by how we respond to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754300,"text":"For the past 15 years,"},{"time":757249,"text":"I've seen the power of this idea"},{"time":759276,"text":"to transform everyday citizens\ninto community health workers --"},{"time":763397,"text":"into everyday heroes."},{"time":766124,"text":"And I've seen it play out everywhere,"},{"time":767950,"text":"from the forest communities\nof West Africa,"},{"time":770032,"text":"to the rural fishing villages of Alaska."},{"time":772979,"text":"It's true,"},{"time":774153,"text":"these community health workers\naren't doing neurosurgery,"},{"time":777226,"text":"but they're making it possible"},{"time":778742,"text":"to bring health care within reach\nof everyone everywhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783645,"text":"So now what?"},{"time":785812,"text":"Well, we know that there are still\nmillions of people dying"},{"time":789600,"text":"from preventable causes"},{"time":791373,"text":"in rural communities around the world."},{"time":793272,"text":"And we know that the great majority\nof these deaths are happening"},{"time":797137,"text":"in these 75 blue-shaded countries."},{"time":799849,"text":"What we also know"},{"time":801024,"text":"is that if we trained an army\nof community health workers"},{"time":804491,"text":"to learn even just 30 lifesaving skills,"},{"time":808508,"text":"we could save the lives of nearly\n30 million people by 2030."},{"time":813652,"text":"Thirty services could save\n30 million lives by 2030."},{"time":818321,"text":"That's not just a blueprint --"},{"time":820088,"text":"we're proving this can be done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821907,"text":"In Liberia,"},{"time":823091,"text":"the Liberian government is training\nthousands of workers like A.B. and Musu"},{"time":827380,"text":"after Ebola,"},{"time":828562,"text":"to bring health care to every\nchild and family in the country."},{"time":832063,"text":"And we've been honored to work with them,"},{"time":834118,"text":"and are now teaming up\nwith a number of organizations"},{"time":836650,"text":"that are working across other countries"},{"time":838896,"text":"to try to help them do the same thing."},{"time":842005,"text":"If we could help these countries scale,"},{"time":845550,"text":"we could save millions of lives,"},{"time":847206,"text":"and at the same time,"},{"time":848586,"text":"we could create millions of jobs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":851875,"text":"We simply can't do that, though,\nwithout technology."},{"time":855286,"text":"People are worried that technology\nis going to steal our jobs,"},{"time":858398,"text":"but when it comes\nto community health workers,"},{"time":860621,"text":"technology has actually\nbeen vital for creating jobs."},{"time":863901,"text":"Without technology --\nwithout this smartphone,"},{"time":866341,"text":"without this rapid test --"},{"time":869960,"text":"it would have been impossible for us\nto be able to employ A.B. and Musu."},{"time":875464,"text":"And I think it's time\nfor technology to help us train,"},{"time":878170,"text":"to help us train people faster\nand better than ever before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":882578,"text":"As a doctor,"},{"time":883752,"text":"I use technology to stay up-to-date\nand keep certified."},{"time":887267,"text":"I use smartphones, I use apps,\nI use online courses."},{"time":889986,"text":"But when A.B. wants to learn,"},{"time":892222,"text":"he's got to jump back in that canoe"},{"time":895152,"text":"and get to the training center."},{"time":896816,"text":"And when Musu shows up for training,"},{"time":899710,"text":"her instructors are stuck using\nflip charts and markers."},{"time":904147,"text":"Why shouldn't they have the same\naccess to learn as I do?"},{"time":910384,"text":"If we truly want community health workers\nto master those lifesaving skills"},{"time":914036,"text":"and even more,"},{"time":916098,"text":"we've got to change this old-school\nmodel of education."},{"time":920282,"text":"Tech can truly be a game changer here."},{"time":922204,"text":"I've been in awe of the digital\neducation revolution"},{"time":925773,"text":"that the likes of Khan Academy\nand edX have been leading."},{"time":930041,"text":"And I've been thinking that it's time;"},{"time":932558,"text":"it's time for a collision"},{"time":933973,"text":"between the digital education revolution"},{"time":936308,"text":"and the community health revolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939483,"text":"And so, this brings me\nto my TED Prize wish."},{"time":943759,"text":"I wish --"},{"time":945584,"text":"I wish that you would help us recruit"},{"time":947814,"text":"the largest army of community health\nworkers the world has ever known"},{"time":952068,"text":"by creating the Community Health Academy,"},{"time":954917,"text":"a global platform to train,\nconnect and empower."}]},{"cues":[{"time":958797,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":959988,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":961175,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":964801,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":967816,"text":"Here's the idea:"},{"time":969384,"text":"we'll create and curate"},{"time":972066,"text":"the best in digital education resources."},{"time":976802,"text":"We will bring those to community\nhealth workers around the world,"},{"time":981461,"text":"including A.B. and Musu."},{"time":982738,"text":"They'll get video lessons\non giving kids vaccines"},{"time":985564,"text":"and have online courses\non spotting the next outbreak,"},{"time":988801,"text":"so they're not stuck using flip charts."},{"time":990708,"text":"We'll help these countries\naccredit these workers,"},{"time":994568,"text":"so that they're not stuck remaining\nan under-recognized, undervalued group,"},{"time":999299,"text":"but become a renowned,\nempowered profession,"},{"time":1002060,"text":"just like nurses and doctors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1005406,"text":"And we'll create a network\nof companies and entrepreneurs"},{"time":1008753,"text":"who've created innovations\nthat can save lives"},{"time":1011053,"text":"and help them connect\nto workers like Musu,"},{"time":1013457,"text":"so she can help better\nserve her community."},{"time":1016959,"text":"And we'll work tirelessly\nto persuade governments"},{"time":1020189,"text":"to make community health workers\na cornerstone of their health care plans."},{"time":1025734,"text":"We plan to test and prototype\nthe academy in Liberia"},{"time":1029547,"text":"and a few other partner countries,"},{"time":1031443,"text":"and then we plan to take it global,"},{"time":1033254,"text":"including to rural North America."},{"time":1036103,"text":"With the power of this platform,"},{"time":1037717,"text":"we believe countries can be more persuaded"},{"time":1040303,"text":"that a health care revolution\nreally is possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1044470,"text":"My dream is that this academy\nwill contribute to the training"},{"time":1048582,"text":"of hundreds of thousands\nof community members"},{"time":1050818,"text":"to help bring health care\nto their neighbors --"},{"time":1053741,"text":"the hundreds of millions of them"},{"time":1055375,"text":"that live in the world's most\nremote communities,"},{"time":1058785,"text":"from the forest communities\nof West Africa,"},{"time":1060890,"text":"to the fishing villages of rural Alaska;"},{"time":1063054,"text":"from the hilltops of Appalachia,\nto the mountains of Afghanistan."},{"time":1067140,"text":"If this vision is aligned with yours,"},{"time":1069854,"text":"head to communityhealthacademy.org,"},{"time":1073740,"text":"and join this revolution."},{"time":1076536,"text":"Let us know if you or your organization\nor someone you know could help us"},{"time":1081213,"text":"as we try to build this academy\nover the next year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1085574,"text":"Now, as I look out into this room,"},{"time":1088310,"text":"I realize that our journeys\nare not self-made;"},{"time":1091040,"text":"they're shaped by others."},{"time":1092573,"text":"And there have been so many here\nthat have been part of this cause."},{"time":1096440,"text":"We're so honored to be part\nof this community,"},{"time":1099674,"text":"and a community that's willing\nto take on a cause"},{"time":1102381,"text":"as audacious as this one,"},{"time":1103773,"text":"so I wanted to offer, as I end,"},{"time":1105872,"text":"a reflection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1107986,"text":"I think a lot more about\nwhat my father taught me."},{"time":1111726,"text":"These days, I too have become a dad."},{"time":1113951,"text":"I have two sons,"},{"time":1115991,"text":"and my wife and I just learned\nthat she's pregnant with our third child."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1120003,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1121035,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1122126,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1124056,"text":"I was recently caring\nfor a woman in Liberia"},{"time":1126908,"text":"who, like my wife,\nwas in her third pregnancy."},{"time":1130371,"text":"But unlike my wife,"},{"time":1132958,"text":"had had no prenatal care\nwith her first two babies."},{"time":1137549,"text":"She lived in an isolated community\nin the forest that had gone for 100 years"},{"time":1141965,"text":"without any health care"},{"time":1144513,"text":"until ..."},{"time":1146165,"text":"until last year when a nurse\ntrained her neighbors"},{"time":1149572,"text":"to become community health workers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1151307,"text":"So here I was,"},{"time":1152623,"text":"seeing this patient\nwho was in her second trimester,"},{"time":1156887,"text":"and I pulled out the ultrasound\nto check on the baby,"},{"time":1160183,"text":"and she started telling us stories\nabout her first two kids,"},{"time":1163746,"text":"and I had the ultrasound\nprobe on her belly,"},{"time":1166968,"text":"and she just stopped mid-sentence."},{"time":1171221,"text":"She turned to me and she said,"},{"time":1172786,"text":"\"Doc, what's that sound?\""},{"time":1177371,"text":"It was the first time she'd ever heard\nher baby's heartbeat."},{"time":1182111,"text":"And her eyes lit up in the same way\nmy wife's eyes and my own eyes lit up"},{"time":1187195,"text":"when we heard our baby's heartbeat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1191544,"text":"For all of human history,"},{"time":1193721,"text":"illness has been universal\nand access to care has not."},{"time":1198277,"text":"But as a wise man once told me:"},{"time":1201690,"text":"no condition is permanent."},{"time":1205491,"text":"It's time."},{"time":1206743,"text":"It's time for us to go as far as it takes"},{"time":1209090,"text":"to change this condition together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1211694,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1212872,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}